Alexander H. GLENN, also Known as Tiny Glenn, et al., Appellants, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 12421. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit. April 15, 1949. J. M. Johnson and A. L. Henson, both of Atlanta, Ga., J. L. Davis, of Cartcrsville, Ga., Graham Wright, of Rome, Ga., and Moses E. Brinson, of Summerville, Ga., for appellants. J. Ellis Mundy, U. S. Atty., of Atlanta, Ga., for appellee.

Before HOLMES, McCORD, and WALLER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the judgment appealed from be, and the same hereby is, affirmed.
